articles.description: Virginia is the top overall seed in the preliminary NCAA tournament bracket preview, with Villanova, Xavier and Purdue earning the other top seeds.

images.caption: The No. 2 Cavaliers force overtime with a pair of late buckets from Ty Jerome, but in the extra session, the Hokies' Kerry Blackshear Jr. scores an and-1 with under 10 seconds remaining for a 61-60 victory.

articles.description: Marvin Bagley III, who suffered a mild right knee sprain Thursday, will miss Duke's game against Georgia Tech on Sunday as a precaution.

videos.description: Dakota Mathias drains a triple as Purdue continues to dominate from the 3-point line.
videos.headline: Mathias leads Purdue with third 3-pointer

videos.description: Jordan Poole drives to the net and stops short as Carsen Edwards leaps for the block and ends up jumping over him.
videos.headline: Poole is hurdled by Edwards after stopping short

videos.description: Zavier Simpson drives full court and drains a jumper at the halftime buzzer.
videos.headline: Simpson takes it coast to coast for buzzer-beater

videos.description: Isaiah Livers hits two consecutive 3-pointers to close the gap on Purdue.
videos.headline: Livers tops off Michigan's 9-0 run with 3-pointer

videos.description: Zavier Simpson draws the defender and makes a nice move on drive to the hoop and finishes with a reverse layup.
videos.headline: Simpson's studder-step to reverse lay-in

videos.description: Michigan forces Purdue to lose the ball and Isaiah Livers scoops it up to take it all the way to the house.
videos.headline: Michigan stellar defense ends in Livers dunk

videos.description: Muhammad-Ali Abdur-Rahkman drives to the hoop and is rejected bu Matt Haarms.
videos.headline: Haarms denies Abdur-Rahkman

videos.description: Zavier Simpson sinks a 3-pointer from far to give the Wolverines their first lead of the night.
videos.headline: Simpson drains NBA 3-pointer for Michigan's first lead

videos.description: With Michigan down 70-69, Charles Matthews throws it up from half court and just misses, sealing No. 5 Purdue's victory.
videos.headline: Matthews just misses potential game winner

videos.description: No. 5 Purdue's Isaac Haas talks about huge 70-69 victory over Michigan.
videos.headline: Haas all smiles after his first win in the Crisler Center
